    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A camera object defines a point above the map’s surface from which to view the map. Applying a camera to a map can have the effect of giving the map a 3D-like appearance. You can use a camera to rotate the map so that it is oriented to match the user’s heading or to apply a pitch angle to tilt the plane of the map. (You can check the map’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/mapkit/mkmapview/1452265-pitchenabled"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to determine whether the map can be pitched.)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Assigning a new camera to this property updates the map immediately and without animating the change. If you want to animate changes in camera position, use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/mapkit/mkmapview/1452476-setcamera"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method instead. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You must not set this property to "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "nil"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". To restore the map to a flat appearance, apply a camera with a pitch angle of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which yields a camera looking straight down onto the map surface. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
